        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] add live provider E2E workflow",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a manual `Live Provider E2E` GitHub Actions workflow that expands a selected provider list into one smoke job per built-in provider\n- add `scripts/live-provider-e2e.sh` to run fast provider-specific smoke checks, skip missing secret/tool setup when requested, and clean up leases where supported\n- document the maintainer secret checklist and workflow controls in `docs/features/live-provider-e2e.md`\n\n## Notes\n\nThe workflow is `workflow_dispatch` only, defaults to `allow_missing=true`, and does not expose provider secrets to pull request jobs. Maintainers can switch `allow_missing=false` once the selected provider secrets are expected to be present.\n\nSome providers still require a runner-side CLI or provider-side resource that cannot be represented as a GitHub secret, such as `devbox`, `sprite`, an existing Railway service, or a self-hosted Parallels host. Those requirements are called out in the doc.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `bash -n scripts/live-provider-e2e.sh`\n- `ruby -e 'require \"yaml\"; YAML.load_file(\".github/workflows/live-provider-e2e.yml\"); puts \"workflow yaml ok\"'`\n- `go build -trimpath -o /tmp/crabbox-provider-e2e ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `node scripts/check-docs-links.mjs`\n- `CRABBOX_LIVE=1 CRABBOX_LIVE_SKIP_MISSING=1 CRABBOX_BIN=/tmp/crabbox-provider-e2e scripts/live-provider-e2e.sh aws`\n- `CRABBOX_LIVE=1 CRABBOX_LIVE_SKIP_MISSING=1 CRABBOX_BIN=/tmp/crabbox-provider-e2e scripts/live-provider-e2e.sh e2b`\n",
